      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\sin\\theta + \\dots + \\sin4\\theta\n                  = 2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta(4\\cos^2\\theta + 2\\cos\\theta - 1)\n                  = 4\\sin( 5\\theta/2 )\\cos\\theta\\cos( \\theta/2 )$\n\n               $4\\cos^2\\theta + 2\\cos\\theta - 1 = 0 \\iff\n                  \\cos\\theta = \\frac {\\sqrt5 -1}4 = \\cos( 2\\pi/5 )\n                  \\text{ ou }\n                  \\cos\\theta = -\\frac {\\sqrt5 +1}4 = \\sin( 2\\pi/5 )$\n\n               $ \\Rightarrow $ modulo $2\\pi$,\n               $\\theta \\in \\{ 0, \\pi, \\pi/2, 3\\pi/2, 2\\pi/5, 4\\pi/5,\n                                   6\\pi/5, 8\\pi/5 \\}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sin\\theta + \\dots + \\sin4\\theta\n                  = 2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta(4\\cos^2\\theta + 2\\cos\\theta -\n1)\n                  = 4\\sin( 5\\theta/2 )\\cos\\theta\\cos( \\theta/2\n)\\)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(4\\cos^2\\theta + 2\\cos\\theta - 1 = 0 \\iff\n                  \\cos\\theta = \\frac {\\sqrt5 -1}4 = \\cos( 2\\pi/5 )\n                  \\text{ ou }\n                  \\cos\\theta = -\\frac {\\sqrt5 +1}4 = \\sin( 2\\pi/5\n)\\)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Rightarrow\\)</span> modulo <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(2\\pi\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\theta\n\\in \\{ 0, \\pi, \\pi/2, 3\\pi/2, 2\\pi/5, 4\\pi/5,\n                                   6\\pi/5, 8\\pi/5 \\}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
